---

<DocsLayout title="Customization - PrismChart - Docs" sidebar={sidebar} toc={toc} issuesUrl="https://github.com/ether-strannik/PrismChart/issues">
	<style>
		h1 {
			font-size: 1.8rem;
			font-weight: 600;
			margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		}

		.tagline {
			color: #666;
			margin-bottom: 2rem;
		}

		h2 {
			font-size: 1.2rem;
			font-weight: 600;
			margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
			padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
			border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
		}

		p {
			color: #333;
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
		}

		.section-intro {
			font-weight: 500;
			color: #000;
			margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		}

		code {
			background: #f5f5f5;
			padding: 0.2em 0.4em;
			border-radius: 3px;
			font-size: 0.9em;
		}

		.video-container {
			margin-bottom: 2rem;
			border-radius: 8px;
			overflow: hidden;
		}

		.video-container iframe {
			display: block;
			width: 100%;
			aspect-ratio: 16/9;
			border: none;
		}
	</style>

	<h1>Customization</h1>
	<p class="tagline">Colors, templates, and profiles</p>

	<div class="video-container" id="video">
		<div id="yt-player"></div>
	</div>

	<script>
		function initYouTubePlayer() {
			const container = document.getElementById('yt-player');
			if (!container || container.hasChildNodes()) return;

			new YT.Player('yt-player', {
				videoId: 'VIDEO_ID_HERE',
				playerVars: { rel: 0, modestbranding: 1 },
				events: {
					onReady: function(e) { e.target.setPlaybackQuality('hd720'); }
				}
			});
		}

		document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', () => {
			if (typeof YT !== 'undefined' && YT.Player) {
				initYouTubePlayer();
			} else {
				const tag = document.createElement('script');
				tag.src = 'https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api';
				document.head.appendChild(tag);
				window.onYouTubeIframeAPIReady = initYouTubePlayer;
			}
		});
	</script>

	<h2 id="color-manager">Color Manager</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Build your own color palette.</p>
	<p>The Color Manager lets you create a custom palette for your drawings. Add colors using hex input (#RRGGBB format) and remove ones you don't need. Your palette persists across sessions - it saves to settings automatically.</p>

	<h2 id="templates">Templates</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Save and reuse object styles.</p>
	<p>Templates capture the appearance of a drawing - color, width, style, fill state, and text properties. Create a template from any selected object, then apply it to others of the same type. Rectangle templates work with rectangles, line templates with lines.</p>
	<p>The Template Manager organizes templates by groups or categories. Complex templates support multi-object setups, saving the style of related objects together. All templates persist to INI files.</p>

	<h2 id="profiles">Profiles</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Save your entire workspace configuration.</p>
	<p>Profiles store your toolbar settings - colors, layers, width, style, font, and layer selection. Save different setups for different trading styles or symbols, then switch between them.</p>
	<p>The default profile (default.ini) auto-loads when PrismChart starts. Use the Save/Load buttons in the Settings dialog to manage profiles. Profile files are stored in <code>MQL5/Files/DrawingLayers/</code>.</p>
</DocsLayout>
